@vincbeck I’d love to pick this one up to help!

My plan is to spin up a local Airflow environment configured with the AwsEcsExecutor, provision two distinct teams, and give them different ECS configurations (e.g., routing to two separate ECS clusters or using different task definitions). I'll then trigger runs for both teams and verify via the AWS console and Airflow logs that the workloads are isolated and routed correctly.

How would you like the test results documented? (e.g., screenshots of the Airflow UI and AWS console, log snippets, or just a summary report here on the issue?)

